reviewText: Quite easily the worst movie I have ever seen. I think I made a better movie in middle school

I'm a fan of Dirt Track racing and I wanted to like this film.  But that bad acting was too much to deal with.  It was completely unbearable to watch. When I say bad acting, that is an understatement.
As a motorsports enthusiast and dirt track racer myself, this is one of the worst, confusing, cheesy as hell movies I've ever seen. Absolutely terrible and disappointing.

You won't find any Oscar worthy performances and the level of cheesiness may make you cringe at moments but if you love racing, your favorite smell is race fumes, you hear "Friday and Saturday Night" and you think racing not clubs, and you have racing in your bloodline you may just enjoy this movie.
Arrived in great shape, woorked well.
Terrible. The poster cover is the best part of the movie. Terrible script, awful acting and poor cinematography makes this one of the worst movies I ever saw.
This is a low budget film that jumped around alot and didn't really follow a good story line but as a big dirt track fan I enjoyed it and understood the point of the movie.
